FBIS4-33307 "drlat108_b_94011" FBIS-LAT-94-108 Daily Report 3 Jun 1994 Curacao Jamaica Senator Backs Hanging Following U.S. Tourist's Death Senator Backs Hanging Following U.S. Tourist's Death FL0306175794 Kingston RJR Network in English 1700 GMT 3 Jun 94 FL0306175794 Kingston RJR Network English BFN [Text] Opposition Senator Dr. [name indistinct] has called for the immediate resumption of hanging. Speaking in the Senate a short while ago, he said the country is in a state of crisis and the security budget needed to reflect the seriousness of the situation. Dr. [name indistinct] was speaking against the background of the recent killing of an American tourist in Runaway Bay. [Words indistinct] (?due to the fact) that a television crew from the BBC was now in Jamaica with regards to that crime. He said their coverage of it was likely to do major damage to Jamaica's reputation.
